splunk> blaze
=======
A blazingly fast frontend with arrow key bindings using the Facebook http://www.tornadoweb.org web framework and http://www.splunk.com search engine.

Put this in your pipe and smoke it!

Installation
=======
Install Tornado:
http://www.tornadoweb.org/

Install Splunk:
http://www.splunk.com/download

Install Splunk Python SDK (Optional)
This is not necessary if you are running this on the same machine as splunk.
http://code.google.com/p/splunk-python-sdk/

Run Splunk Blaze:
#Download http://github.com/docyes/splunk_blaze/tarball/master 
tar zvzf docyes-splunk-blaze-*.tar.gz
cd docyes-splunk-blaze-*
#Make splunkblaze.py executable.
chmod u+x splunkblaze.py
#Checkout the nifty command line options.
#Command line formats are what you would expect ("--myoption=myvalue")
./splunkblaze.py --help
#Blaze! (Default port is 8888)
./splunkblaze.py

Know Issues:
=======
-Safari key bindings not working.

Future Features:
-Faster!